{
  "texts": [
    "The impact of COVID-19 in the UAE and Malaysia, although unique to each nation's context, reflects broader global trends, while emphasizing specific regional characteristics.",
    "In the UAE, the existing healthcare infrastructure and strong government response have been critical, while Malaysia has navigated through challenges with community engagement and resilience.",
    "Economic consequences in both nations have led to reflection and restructuring, which may shape future growth patterns.",
    "This understanding forms the basis for further exploration of predictive models and the role of deep learning in healthcare, particularly in contexts defined by complexity and dynamism [16, 36, 37].",
    "Deep learning in healthcare presents a myriad of ethical challenges starting with data privacy."
  ]
}